Project

Build a multilingual B2B website for Dome Auctions with:

Next.js App Router

Sanity Studio v3

Tailwind CSS

Vercel deployment

HubSpot forms

locales: nl-be and fr-be

The site has 2 content pillars:

Insights / Blog

Sector Landing Pages

This is not a generic marketing site.
It must feel industrial, calm, competent, trustworthy, editable, and scalable.

Core Rules

Use TypeScript.

Use Server Components by default.

Use 'use client' only when required.

Follow the existing project structure first.

Do not refactor unrelated files.

Do not invent a new architecture if the current one already works.

Before changing middleware, routing, schema structure, or shared layout logic, first explain the plan.

Keep code production-ready.

Prefer reusable components over one-off implementations.

Never hardcode important page content in page files if it belongs in Sanity or translation files.

Content Strategy
Mandatory

Use separate translated documents.

Do not use bilingual fields like title.nl / title.fr for core editorial content.

Each language version must be its own Sanity document.

All translations must be linked via a translation relationship strategy.

Use this content split

Editorial content → Sanity

Structured page content → Sanity

UI labels / interface text → translation files

Reusable system strings → messages files

Languages

Supported locales:

nl-be

fr-be

Requirements:

All public pages must support both locales unless explicitly stated otherwise.

Metadata must be language-specific.

Slugs may differ by language if needed.

Fallbacks must be explicit, never accidental.

Routing Rules
Phase 1

Only implement locale-based routing first:

/nl-be/...

/fr-be/...

Phase 2

Hostname/subdomain routing only after phase 1 is stable:

woodworking.dome-auctions.com

metalworking.dome-auctions.com

construction.dome-auctions.com

agriculture.dome-auctions.com

transport.dome-auctions.com

Important

Do not start with hostname-based routing.

